cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with network slicing, which is a key enabler for the future 5G networks. It also discusses the resource provisioning approach for network slices, which is a crucial aspect of network architecture. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it proposes a method to manage and control the resources of a network infrastructure. 

The sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the allocation of resources across a set of network slices, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 

The sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) is another possibility as the paper discusses the aggregation of resource demands within a graph, which can be seen as a form of information compression. 

Finally, the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) is a possibility as the paper deals with the deployment of Service Function Chains (SFCs) within a slice, which can be seen as a security concern.
